trend_summary: 2000-20xx imagery shows gradual suburban build-out. Forest and pasture in the south are cleared, first as construction sites, then a large school, stadium and parking appear. Residential cul-de-sacs extend westward and infill between existing estates, raising built-up coverage but green canopy still dominates. No high-rise or industrial growth.
notable_changes: Central-south forest cleared and replaced by a large school campus with stadium and parking lots.
Expansion of residential cul-de-sac neighbourhoods, especially toward the southwest and north-central areas.
Infill construction along existing streets reduces vacant lots and increases roof density.
New local roads added, improving internal connectivity across housing clusters.
